regularly approved compensation for Mr. Levin in excess of the cap=E2=80=9D=
 on his pay in the Rithm deal. Also Sculptor  says=C2=A0that =E2=80=9CMr. O=
ch=E2=80=99s purported concern for public stockholders is in stark contrast=
 to his record when running the Company. Mr. Och took home $3.3 billion sin=
ce 2007 while the Company=E2=80=99s stock price dropped by 96%.=E2=80=9D Th=
