 but it doesn=E2=80=99t have to pay the benefits all at once. Och, accordin=
g to Sculptor, wanted the buyer to make the payments all at once=C2=A0as a =
condition of his support.=09The rollover: Och=C2=A0still has lots of partne=
rship units that he hasn=E2=80=99t yet converted into stock. One normal way=
 to do a cash merger of Sculptor would be to convert all of Och=E2=80=99s p=
artnership units into Sculptor shares and then cash them out at $11.15, the=
 same price as the public shareholders. But this would require him to immed=
iately pay taxes on the $11.15 of proceeds. Which doesn=E2=80=99t sound tha=
